The paper is about optimization algorithms, specifically the covariance matrix adaptation evolution strategy (CMA-ES) and the continuous non-revisiting genetic algorithm (cNrGA). Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of search history and binary space partitioning, which are common techniques in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper presents experimental results and performance analysis, which are typical of data science (cs.DS) and systems and control (cs.SY) sub-categories.
